<dl id="n36129d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36129d">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36129d"> 129(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Ragged Schools Union</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The British and Foreign School Society (1808) and the National Society (1811), together with <mark>the Ragged Schools Union</mark> (1844), were the only special organizations providing for the education of the poorer classes until 1870. <small> &ldquo;LONDON&rdquo; <a name="EBLO" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBLO"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 947</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
